jbnb: Try this approach on this release:

1. Get gmaptool v0.20 (google gmaptool)
2. Get Jetmose keygen
3. Generate a valid code for your GPS with Jetmouse kg. Fill in your unit ID and under Select map product you choose  fill in 284 there and then click the generate button at the bottom. Now you have your unlock code.
4. run gmaptool from command line window like this: gmaptool -U 1234567890123456789012345 gmapprom.img
Replace 1234567890123456789012345 with the unlock code from step 3.
5. This will insert the correct code for your unit into the gmapprom.img file.
6. copy over the modyfied gmapprom.img to your memcard in the GPS, place it in the garmin folder..
7. thats it, if it doesent work try rename the gmapprom.img to gmapsupp.img.

Okay, so all you guys failing to unlock according to your Garmin... the Card ID that Garmin Keygen is looking for, is NOT your SERIAL number, printed on the outside of your Garmin GPS.

Instead, enter the GPS Tool's menu, Settings, System, About... you'll find an all digits-number right below the software version. On a Nüvi 200, this is a ten digit number. That's the one you wanna punch into the key generator!

So, map code 284 is correct.
